00:56:37.794 --> 00:56:39.847
And the Lord said, 'Lay hold to it.

00:56:39.847 --> 00:56:46.027
' He said, 'There's many of you that have not been obedient to doing what He's asking you to do.

00:56:46.027 --> 00:56:48.451
You've pushed it away.

00:56:48.975 --> 00:56:56.359
You have a call on your life and you've not yielded to it.

00:56:56.359 --> 00:57:05.560
You've not been obedient to what God's called you to do.

00:57:05.560 --> 00:57:08.113
It's all hands on deck right now.

00:57:08.113 --> 00:57:13.920
For the harvest is plentiful and the laborers are few.

00:57:13.920 --> 00:57:25.400
Will you obey what God has called you to do in these last days and stop running from Him?

00:57:25.400 --> 00:57:33.380
He's going to bypass you and go to the next person if you keep putting up your hands and say He's out of time.

00:57:33.380 --> 00:57:33.555
He's not begging you.

00:57:33.555 --> 00:57:33.905
'You?

00:57:33.905 --> 00:57:35.194
You're only 15.

00:57:35.194 --> 00:57:36.680
I don't care.

00:57:36.680 --> 00:57:37.205
Come on.

00:57:37.205 --> 00:57:37.905
How old are you?

00:57:37.905 --> 00:57:38.530
You're 12.

00:57:38.530 --> 00:57:39.430
Let's do it.

00:57:39.430 --> 00:57:42.966
' Nothing's going to disqualify you.

00:57:42.966 --> 00:57:46.380
Keep underneath the mighty hand of the Lord and humble yourself.

00:57:46.380 --> 00:57:47.940
Keep out of sin.

00:57:47.940 --> 00:57:55.320
Keep yourself right before Him by prayer and fasting, seeking Him daily.

00:57:55.320 --> 00:58:07.427
Now, if you fall down in sin, you run to God when you sin; you don't run away from Him.

00:58:24.480 --> 00:58:24.650
I'm not saying that any of us are perfect.

00:58:24.650 --> 00:58:32.864
But I'm not saying you deliberately practice and do things that you know you shouldn't be doing.

00:58:32.864 --> 00:58:42.740
Now, if you mess up in life and you drop a bad word or something, people mess up.

00:58:42.740 --> 00:58:45.980
I'm talking about people who are deliberately...

00:58:45.980 --> 00:58:48.885
you know what, bud?

00:58:48.885 --> 00:58:53.587
Let's go to the strip club this weekend and we'll repent on Sunday.

00:58:53.587 --> 00:58:55.630
Let's go out and get drunk tonight.

00:58:55.630 --> 00:59:00.630
Let's go get wasted.

00:59:08.488 --> 00:59:08.856
You know that's wrong, but you do it because, you know what?

00:59:08.856 --> 00:59:12.889
It's okay; God knows it's under grace.

00:59:13.098 --> 00:59:18.590
You know, it's okay to cheat on your wife or husband or whatever; I'll repent about it.

00:59:18.590 --> 00:59:20.497
She's not fulfilling my needs.

00:59:20.497 --> 00:59:22.707
He's not fulfilling my needs.

00:59:28.320 --> 00:59:31.040
So, I'm just going to go out and, you know, we have an open marriage; it's cool.

00:59:41.480 --> 00:59:42.438
It's wrong, and you know it's wrong, but yet you keep dipping in.

00:59:53.840 --> 00:59:55.235
The wages of sin is death, and that's what I'm talking about.

01:00:07.309 --> 01:00:07.651
You know it's wrong, and you keep trying.

01:00:09.320 --> 01:00:09.640
You keep doing the same thing over.

01:00:09.800 --> 01:00:19.143
You don't run to God; you run to the devil and his crowd and think, 'Well, I'm saved by grace.

01:00:19.143 --> 01:00:22.000
I can live both sides.

01:00:22.000 --> 01:00:29.860
One foot is over here and I have one foot over there, and we're okay.

01:00:29.860 --> 01:00:36.149
' And those are the ones I'm talking about right now.

01:00:41.416 --> 01:00:41.760
It's time to be all in.

01:00:41.760 --> 01:00:53.400
It's time to sell out for Jesus, to look at Him as a holy God, and we are made in His image and we need to be holy as He is holy.

01:00:53.400 --> 01:01:05.787
I'm going to do everything I can to be as far away from the world and what they want and what they think is cool.

01:01:05.787 --> 01:01:14.160
I want to be as close as I can to Him, sitting in His lap, listening to His breath.

01:01:14.160 --> 01:01:19.086
What can I do to be closer to Him?

01:01:19.086 --> 01:01:28.870
I'm not just right on the edge of living in the world and barely in the church; I want to be all in.

01:01:28.870 --> 01:01:33.289
I want to know what His breath smells like if He has breath.

01:01:33.289 --> 01:01:49.240
If He has bad breath that day, which I'm sure He doesn't, but if He did, I want to know that He did, or what kind of fragrance He had.

01:01:49.240 --> 01:01:51.800
'Did you spray some cologne on, Lord?

01:01:51.800 --> 01:01:54.230
I want to know what You have on today.

01:01:54.230 --> 01:01:55.390
What is it?

01:01:55.390 --> 01:01:56.860
Is it frankincense today?

01:01:56.860 --> 01:02:04.600
' I want that because I'm that close.

01:02:04.600 --> 01:02:07.646
I just want to know Him.

01:02:12.440 --> 01:02:17.620
And I know that when you seek Him, you will find Him because I have those moments like I had last night.

01:02:18.240 --> 01:02:22.590
And I could see all that was coming.

01:02:41.800 --> 01:02:42.046
And after it was over, the presence filled me.

01:02:42.046 --> 01:02:44.747
I could feel it all day today quietly.

01:02:44.747 --> 01:02:49.389
I learned to get quieter as I talked to my friend Billy Burke.

01:02:49.389 --> 01:02:51.320
He's not a chatterbox.

01:02:51.320 --> 01:02:57.460
He stays to himself, and you learn from people who walk with Him.

01:02:57.460 --> 01:02:59.756
What does it take?

01:02:59.756 --> 01:03:04.480
And what does God say about you whenever I get off the phone with you?

01:03:09.150 --> 01:03:09.700
Not that I'm perfect, but it's always a fragrance.

01:03:09.700 --> 01:03:15.210
What is the fragrance that you leave in His nostrils?

01:03:15.210 --> 01:03:17.320
Does He call you friend?

01:03:17.320 --> 01:03:21.440
I love it whenever the Lord says to me, 'Billy's my friend.

01:03:21.440 --> 01:03:25.510
' Walk carefully when you talk that way to Him.

01:03:25.510 --> 01:03:26.733
'He's my friend.

01:03:26.733 --> 01:03:28.200
' It challenges me.

01:03:28.200 --> 01:03:30.554
I go, 'He's Your friend.

01:03:30.554 --> 01:03:36.000
' Honor Him when you're on the phone.

01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:36.660
Say this.

01:03:36.660 --> 01:03:38.720
Don't say that.

01:03:38.720 --> 01:03:39.787
Don't ever say that.

01:03:39.787 --> 01:03:40.640
Don't disrespect Him.

01:03:40.640 --> 01:03:46.187
He corrects me about certain things, and I'm just a young guy.

01:03:46.187 --> 01:03:53.360
Some things, like I said earlier, just dumb things sometimes come out of your mouth when you chatter.

01:03:55.730 --> 01:03:57.320
You talk to somebody that's older and the Lord says, 'Hush.

01:03:57.320 --> 01:04:02.931
' What does the Father think about you?

01:04:02.931 --> 01:04:17.425
What is the fragrance that you leave around Him?

01:04:36.520 --> 01:04:41.994
I want so badly for Him to want to visit my house and feel comfortable here, where He says, 'You know what?

01:05:02.720 --> 01:05:03.856
I can go there and I know I won't be grieved.

01:05:03.856 --> 01:05:11.560
Take not Thy Spirit from me.

01:05:11.560 --> 01:05:41.044
' Kathryn Kuhlman used to say things like that, and I thought she sounded kind of nutty because I was ignorant.

01:05:41.044 --> 01:06:23.320
But the older I get and the more I spend at His feet, I realize there is—like I said, I can feel it when He withdraws like that when I said that about the redhead thing.

01:06:24.760 --> 01:06:28.840
I went, 'Oh, I grieved it.

01:06:28.840 --> 01:06:33.533
It's not right.

01:06:33.533 --> 01:06:36.773
' Repent.

01:06:36.773 --> 01:06:40.390
Be sensitive.

01:06:44.640 --> 01:07:03.760
And the more you spend time with Him, your words are heavy and they have a lot of weight.

01:07:36.571 --> 01:07:38.015
And you'll learn you just can't flap your mouth all the time, especially having Him around.

01:07:38.015 --> 01:07:55.950
He has an opinion about everything.

01:08:21.146 --> 01:08:23.933
The Lord has an opinion about everything.

01:08:23.933 --> 01:08:44.972
And He says, 'Think on these things: whatsoever things are lovely, whatsoever things are pure, whatsoever things are of good report.

01:08:44.972 --> 01:08:52.560
' I could go on and on.

01:08:52.560 --> 01:09:12.903
In 1 Corinthians 13, love takes no account of a suffered wrong.

01:09:26.073 --> 01:09:26.480
I don't know how many times He corrects me about love.

01:09:26.480 --> 01:09:40.152
But faith works by love, and God is love, and the greater part of the anointing is walking in love.

01:09:54.120 --> 01:09:54.976
The angels visited.

01:09:54.976 --> 01:10:20.620
I remember I told you they said that he doesn't realize that most of what he gets before the Father, he'll be judged upon—what he's judged upon the most—is: how did he walk in love?

01:10:20.620 --> 01:10:23.527
How did he treat his fellow brethren?

01:10:23.527 --> 01:10:25.965
How did he walk in love?

01:10:25.965 --> 01:10:31.870
How did you treat people when you think you're better than them?

01:10:31.880 --> 01:10:36.880
Do you bless them?

01:10:36.880 --> 01:10:57.600
Do you help the waiter out at the table that's serving you, and they may have had a rough day?

01:10:57.600 --> 01:11:24.710
Do you treat them with honor and give them a good tip, or do you just give a little bit?

01:11:24.720 --> 01:11:30.658
'Here's a buck.

01:11:30.658 --> 01:11:45.867
' What are you going to do with a dollar?

01:11:45.867 --> 01:11:51.394
She has to feed her family.

01:11:51.394 --> 01:12:22.460
If you can't afford to give a tip, don't go out to eat then.

01:12:22.460 --> 01:12:37.112
I say go through the drive-thru, but don't treat people bad.

01:12:37.112 --> 01:12:42.425
I always try to walk in love.

01:12:42.425 --> 01:12:50.717
I'm not always saying that I've been good at that, but the Lord rebukes me about certain things now.

01:13:08.720 --> 01:13:09.023
And He'll say, 'Brandon, that's a poverty mentality.

01:13:09.023 --> 01:13:15.747
What you're doing and how you just acted right then is poverty.

01:13:15.747 --> 01:13:18.400
' I say, 'Break poverty.

01:13:18.400 --> 01:13:20.469
' It's a mindset.

01:13:20.469 --> 01:13:22.000
It's a stronghold.

01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:32.164
Break poverty off of your life by how you think and how you act, how you sow, what you're believing, what you're saying.

01:13:44.180 --> 01:13:57.680
So when I saw it last night and I saw all that, I was bothered—not because of what I saw, but because there are so many of you that have no idea what's coming and you're not ready.

01:13:57.680 --> 01:14:15.030
And I've tried so hard to convey to you: it's time for you to learn how to believe God for five dollars.

01:14:15.030 --> 01:14:26.418
It's time for you to believe—what if there was no way for you to go get a surgery and you really needed it?

01:14:26.418 --> 01:14:35.103
Can you believe God for a toenail that hurts?

01:14:38.206 --> 01:14:56.144
When it comes down to it and we're in the end times and we see these things around us, could I believe for the impossible—the surgery—that God would come through?

01:14:58.676 --> 01:15:01.772
I saw people around tables that had nothing, and they would hold their hands.

01:15:01.772 --> 01:15:08.611
I saw pots of food fill up with beans and cornbread and potatoes.

01:15:10.173 --> 01:15:15.720
I saw families that had steaming pots of food within just seconds when they gave grace.

01:15:15.720 --> 01:15:19.240
God showed up and did a miracle.

01:15:19.240 --> 01:15:39.031
Now, I've heard of other people having the same kind of visions, but the Lord warned me and He said, 'Brandon, the Bible says I've never seen the righteous forsaken or a seed begging bread.

01:15:39.031 --> 01:15:40.543
Either you believe it or you don't.

01:15:40.543 --> 01:15:43.920
' George Mueller was one of them.

01:15:58.373 --> 01:15:58.591
He had the orphanages and all this.

01:15:59.027 --> 01:16:27.096
He would start out believing for five dollars, and then he said it was just as easy to believe for five dollars as it was for a million later on in his walk with the Lord.

01:16:27.096 --> 01:16:46.360
So he could believe for a million dollars or he could believe for five dollars, but it was the same amount of faith after a while.

01:16:50.618 --> 01:16:53.640
He built himself up to it.

01:16:53.640 --> 01:17:01.920
So a million dollars wasn't much for him anymore, just like five bucks.

01:17:03.360 --> 01:17:03.990
But it took faith and patience.

01:17:03.990 --> 01:17:04.620
Faith works.

01:17:04.620 --> 01:17:04.830
Work it.

01:17:04.830 --> 01:17:05.796
Faith without works is dead.

01:17:05.796 --> 01:17:12.480
So, all right, I've talked too much again tonight, but I've tried to warn you all.

01:17:15.165 --> 01:17:15.500
You better start activating your faith.

01:17:15.500 --> 01:17:17.528
Believe God for the impossible.

01:17:17.528 --> 01:17:19.093
Get in the Word.

01:17:19.093 --> 01:17:32.376
Faith cometh by hearing and hearing by the Word of God.

01:17:32.376 --> 01:17:33.827
That's the only way faith comes.

01:17:33.827 --> 01:17:46.580
'Well, I bet if I had visitations from Jesus, if I had visitations from angels and all the things that you say you've had, Brandon, I bet I'd have great faith.

01:17:46.580 --> 01:17:49.540
' No, it had nothing to do with it.

01:17:49.540 --> 01:17:56.726
Because the moment you have challenges, you doubt those things and it comes up in your heart.

01:18:21.267 --> 01:18:21.773
The only thing that ever keeps me anchored is the word of God.

01:18:21.773 --> 01:18:34.758
Faith comes by hearing, and hearing by the word of God—not an experience.

01:18:34.758 --> 01:18:49.091
I don't care what kind of great experience you've had.

01:18:49.091 --> 01:19:01.716
If you don't have the word of God down inside of your heart, whenever the storms of life come, the experience never will keep you.

01:19:36.212 --> 01:19:37.623
The word will.

01:19:37.623 --> 01:19:45.640
And I've seen Jesus nine times now.

01:19:45.640 --> 01:20:12.330
He visits and I'll talk to him, and I don't say that to brag.

01:20:12.340 --> 01:20:14.480
It's more than that now.

01:20:14.480 --> 01:20:25.672
Because he stood here—he came to the house twice.

01:20:25.672 --> 01:20:38.400
So over the course of my life now, it's going on a lot.

01:20:38.400 --> 01:20:41.280
Why, Brandon?

01:20:41.280 --> 01:20:43.080
Why you?

01:20:43.080 --> 01:20:45.247
I don't know.

01:20:45.247 --> 01:20:52.730
He'll visit any one of you if you seek him.

01:20:52.730 --> 01:20:57.700
I'm just thankful when he does.

01:20:57.700 --> 01:20:58.880
How many angels?

01:20:58.880 --> 01:21:02.640
This is the thing I never tell you.

01:21:02.640 --> 01:21:09.041
You know how many times I see demons?

01:21:09.041 --> 01:21:19.165
More than I see the other, but I never talk about it.

01:21:19.165 --> 01:21:30.240
In fact, I saw three today, but I don't talk about it.

01:21:30.240 --> 01:21:41.760
Why give glory to something that's fallen and has already been defeated with your words?

01:21:41.760 --> 01:21:46.910
Why give them power in your words?

01:21:52.154 --> 01:22:03.564
The more you exalt them—they're exalted by pride—and the more you talk about them, they fluff themselves up.

01:22:03.564 --> 01:22:05.274
Why?

01:22:05.274 --> 01:22:15.810
Because that's what they're after.

01:22:15.810 --> 01:22:20.969
They want you to acknowledge them.

01:22:26.376 --> 01:22:26.800
And the more you acknowledge them—'I see a demon there!

01:22:27.947 --> 01:22:29.343
I see a demon there!

01:22:29.343 --> 01:22:32.948
'—they go, 'Oh, you do?

01:22:38.120 --> 01:22:38.320
You see me?

01:22:38.320 --> 01:22:44.851
' and they get all excited about it because it's all about pride.

01:22:46.634 --> 01:22:51.980
Do you see?

01:22:51.980 --> 01:23:00.537
And so many Christians focus on the demonic way too much.

01:23:04.600 --> 01:23:10.789
I don't talk about it very long.

01:23:10.789 --> 01:23:22.627
And the same thing about witchcraft: I take authority over it and I'll leave it alone.

01:23:22.627 --> 01:23:27.368
Hexes and vexes and all that—it's real.

01:23:27.368 --> 01:23:30.205
But they don't have power over me.

01:23:30.205 --> 01:23:42.015
A curse without a cause cannot stand.

01:23:42.015 --> 01:24:12.060
Greater is he that is in me than he that is in the world.

01:25:01.304 --> 01:25:01.816
A thousand shall fall at our side and 10,000 on our right hand, but nothing shall come nigh us.

01:25:01.816 --> 01:25:04.473
Either you believe it or you don't.

01:25:05.440 --> 01:25:17.109
And this covenant of his blood and what he did for us on that cross—I am seated with him in the heavenlies.

01:25:34.794 --> 01:25:35.229
And when you understand and you're a believing believer and you walk in the authority of the believer, nothing shall by any means hurt you.

01:25:56.398 --> 01:25:57.436
And I say to be absent from the body is to be present with the Lord.

01:25:57.436 --> 01:26:03.360
I have victory no matter what.

01:26:03.360 --> 01:26:14.348
So when I tell you I see demonic stuff, yes, but they're defeated.

01:26:14.348 --> 01:26:20.300
So why talk about something that's been defeated?

01:26:25.164 --> 01:26:30.520
And all these people talking about singing angels and talking angels—I don't believe it.

01:26:30.520 --> 01:26:37.430
Do you know?

01:26:37.440 --> 01:26:40.394
They are always on assignment to give him glory.

01:26:40.394 --> 01:26:44.046
They don't ever bring glory to themselves.

01:26:44.046 --> 01:26:44.629
Never.

01:26:44.629 --> 01:26:47.748
They always are looking to him.

01:26:47.748 --> 01:26:56.820
Every time I've had it, they always are looking to him unless they have a word to tell you.

01:26:59.040 --> 01:27:02.680
And the other night, he had an opal outfit and he stood right over here.

01:27:02.680 --> 01:27:04.053
He was on assignment.

01:27:32.260 --> 01:27:32.624
He gave me a message; he told me what he was supposed to say.

01:27:32.624 --> 01:27:52.000
But the moment he stopped speaking, he didn't look at me like he wanted to have pie and coconut milk and a fistbump.

01:27:52.000 --> 01:27:54.927
He was looking to the Father immediately.

01:27:54.927 --> 01:27:59.628
His eyes were upon our Father, getting strength from him.

01:27:59.628 --> 01:28:04.956
And the moment the angels gaze upon our Lord, they get strength.

01:28:04.956 --> 01:28:06.680
Their skin glows.

01:28:06.680 --> 01:28:11.227
They glow because of the glory.

01:28:11.227 --> 01:28:28.380
So if they're always looking to him and they're around him all the time, how much more should you be looking at him as his child?

01:28:28.380 --> 01:28:34.531
They never have a mission of their own.

01:28:34.531 --> 01:28:38.600
They're on a mission from him to help you.

01:28:38.600 --> 01:28:43.720
They're ministering spirits sent forth to the heirs of salvation.

01:28:43.720 --> 01:28:45.391
That's what the Bible says.

01:28:51.747 --> 01:28:52.053
And then it says we can entertain angels unaware.

01:28:52.053 --> 01:28:52.667
Why?

01:28:52.667 --> 01:28:54.364
Because they're on an assignment.

01:28:54.364 --> 01:29:06.392
Things can happen because he's sent his angels to keep charge over us, lest they bear us up in their hands, lest we dash our foot against a stone—Psalm 91.

01:29:06.392 --> 01:29:07.658
And I believe it.

01:29:07.658 --> 01:29:08.946
But demons, they're different.

01:29:08.946 --> 01:29:10.295
They are always about themselves.

01:29:10.295 --> 01:29:11.256
They're always wanting attention.

01:29:11.256 --> 01:29:13.880
They always want you to be in fear.

01:29:13.880 --> 01:29:14.760
Fear tolerated is faith contaminated.

01:29:14.760 --> 01:29:16.303
The more you fear them, the more it is faith in their ability to hurt you.

01:29:16.303 --> 01:29:17.996
You have more faith in their ability to hurt you than in God's ability to protect you.

01:29:17.996 --> 01:29:18.472
Fear tolerated is faith contaminated.

01:29:18.472 --> 01:30:04.778
And they will present themselves to you as big as they can so that you'll gaze upon them instead of our Lord Jesus.

01:30:04.778 --> 01:30:58.840
And the more you look at a demon, the more they will get bigger in front of you because they're full of pride.

01:30:58.840 --> 01:31:00.063
It's all about them.

01:31:00.063 --> 01:31:09.465
So if you ever want to know if you're really talking to a demon versus an angel, always look at them if they're around you.

01:31:09.465 --> 01:31:11.720
Look and say, 'Well, I see this.

01:31:11.720 --> 01:31:13.420
What are they doing?

01:31:13.420 --> 01:31:16.930
' They're looking to the Father.

01:31:16.930 --> 01:31:24.390
Angels—demons just want to be exalted.

01:31:24.400 --> 01:31:28.960
Does that help you a little bit?

01:31:28.960 --> 01:32:18.773
So, there's some of you that are having things knocking on your house, waking you up in the middle of the night with cold chills—something of fear.

01:32:18.773 --> 01:32:22.383
You are tormented all the time by demonic spirits.

01:32:22.383 --> 01:32:28.190
Anoint your house with oil and tell that devil to get out.

01:32:28.200 --> 01:32:50.910
Open the door and say, 'You get out of here right now!

01:32:50.910 --> 01:32:53.960
You're not welcome in my house.

01:32:53.960 --> 01:33:26.260
' But there are so many people who play pat-a-cake with Casper.

01:33:26.260 --> 01:33:31.750
